Target: OntoHPLC is an ontology developed for expressing a high performance liquid chromatography.

Comment: A separation technique in which the mobile phase is a liquid. Liquid chromatography can be carried out either in a column or on a plane. Present-day liquid chromatography generally utilizing very small particles and a relatively high inlet pressure is often characterized by the term high-performance (or high-pressure) liquid chromatography, and the acronym HPLC. [https://doi.org/10.1351/goldbook.L03578]
A separation technique in which the mobile phase is a liquid. Here the liquid chromatography is modelled as a saref:Task that can be accomplished by HPLC.
The function to measure the chromatogram of a given chemical solution.
The command to realise "ChromatogramMeasurement" function.
An appearance of one HPLC job.
The report generated during one HPLC job.
One data point that indicates a peak appears in the chromatogram, normally it refers to a phase component.
A compound added to a sample in known concentration to facilitate the qualitative indentification and/or quantitative determination of the sample components. [https://doi.org/10.1351/goldbook.I03108]
The area enclosed between the peak and the baseline. [https://doi.org/10.1351/goldbook.P04453]
The time between injection of sample into HPLC column and emergence of a solute of the sample.

The response factor is defined as the ratio between a signal produced by a solute of the sample and the signal produced by the internal standard of the sample. This ratio is concentration-based in this specific application.
The relation between HighPerformanceLiquidChromatography and the liquid chromatography task it can conduct.
The relation identifies that the HighPerformanceLiquidChromatography that can accomplish the liquid chromatography task.
The relation identifies the chromatogram measurement function of HighPerformanceLiquidChromatography.
The relation between ChromatogramMeasurement function and ChromatogramMeasurementCommander command.
The relation between ChromatogramMeasurementCommander command and ChromatogramMeasurement function it can achieve.
The relation between a HPLC and the HPLC job it conducts.
The relation between a HPLC job and the report it generates.
The relation between a HPLC report and the chromatogram data it records.
The relation between a HPLC report and the chemical solution it is generated for.
The relation between a HPLC report and the HPLC method it is using.
The relation between a HPLC report and the internal standard that was used during generating the report.
The relation between a HPLC method and the response factor of each species under this method.
The relation between a HPLC method and the ideal retention time of each species under this method.
The relation between the chromatogram point and the phase component it refers to.
The relation between the chromatogram point and the peak area it calculated.
The relation between chromatogram point and the retention time at which the point was referring to.
The relationship between the response factor/retention time and the species which the previous quantity is referring to.
